1 susp ected of involvement in terrorism, targeted violence, threats to
2 public safety, or any other threats of organized or violent crime to
3 law enforcement and public safety agencies.
4 C. Any information disseminated pursuant to the provisions of
5 this section shall be confidential, and the recipients of such
6 information shall comply with the handling terms associated with the
7 disclosure. Unauthorized release or unauthorized use of information
8 disseminated pursuant to this section shall be a felony punishable
9 by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for
10 a term not to exceed three (3) years, by a fine not more than Fifty
11 Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00), or by both such imprisonment and
12 fine. Such offense shall also be punishable by termination of
13 employment and revocation of the individual’s certification as a
14 peace officer in this state. As used in this subsection,
15 “unauthorized release” or “unauthorized use” shall include, but not
16 be limited to, disseminating or disclosing confidential information
17 in a manner which exceeds the scope of the handling terms associated
18 with the disclosure or is in violation of any rules promulgated
19 pursuant to this act. Provided, however, the following shall not
20 constitute an unauthorized release or unauthorized use of
21 confidential information disseminated by the Office:
22 1. Sharing the confidential information with a law enforcement
23 officer or prosecutorial authority for use in a criminal
24 investigation or prosecution; or
